  "content_en": "<div class=\"royal-legacy-card\"><div class=\"legacy-section\"><div class=\"legacy-section-header\"><span class=\"legacy-icon\">‚öîÔ∏è</span><h5>Arab Invasion</h5></div><div class=\"legacy-section-content\"><p>Raja Dahir was the last Hindu ruler of Sindh. During his reign, in 712 CE, the Arabs, led by Muhammad bin Qasim, invaded Sindh.</p></div></div><div class=\"legacy-section\"><div class=\"legacy-section-header\"><span class=\"legacy-icon\">üõ°Ô∏è</span><h5>Battle of Rewar</h5></div><div class=\"legacy-section-content\"><p>Dahir bravely confronted the Arab army in the <strong>Battle of Rewar (Battle of Rewar/Aror)</strong> but was killed in the battle. His wives and daughters also fought to defend the fort and committed Jauhar. This event marked the beginning of a new chapter in Indian history.</p></div></div></div>"
